README - Bouncing ball game (English)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Introduction
Welcome to the Pygame Brick Breaker! This project is a simple yet engaging brick breaker game built using the Pygame library. The game involves controlling a paddle to bounce a ball and break bricks. It includes features like a main menu, pause menu, game over screen, and score tracking.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Features
Interactive Visualizations: Watch the brick-breaking process in real-time with visual representations.
Multiple Difficulty Levels: Support for various difficulty levels with different brick layouts.
Educational Tool: Designed to improve understanding of physics and game mechanics through visual and interactive learning aids.
Adjustable Speed: Modify the ball speed to make the game more challenging.
User-Friendly Interface: Simple and intuitive interface for an optimal gaming experience.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Use
Install Python: Ensure you have Python installed on your system.
Clone Repository: Clone this repository to your local machine.
Navigate to Directory: Open a terminal and navigate to the project directory.
Install Dependencies: Run the following command to install the required dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt
Launch Application: Execute the script by running:
python main.py
Play the Game: Use the arrow keys to move the paddle and bounce the ball. Try to break all the bricks without letting the ball fall.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Technologies Used
Python: The core programming language used for development.
Pygame: A library for making video games in Python.
Sys: A Python module that provides access to some variables used or maintained by the interpreter.
Os: A Python module that provides a way of using operating system dependent functionality.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Acknowledgments
Special thanks to the developers and community behind Python and Pygame for providing the tools to create this game. Enjoy playing and improving your skills!
Feel free to reach out with any questions or feedback!

